  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Ghana Tax Dialogue</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project introduces an innovative approach to pursuing fiscal justice through multi -stakeholder dialogue that is intended to achieve a change in corporate tax practice within the private sector. It seeks to engage the private sector in recognising corporate taxation as a central theme of Corporate Social Responsibility (CSR) and as an issue that is relevant to the business and human rights agenda.  Through the constructive multi -stakeholder dialogue, the project expects to:  &#xB7; Identify and understand business&apos; role in establishing a fair tax system in Ghana that ensures financing for human rights by placing corporate tax at the heart of sustainable business practices. &#xB7; Unpacking and agreeing upon what constitutes responsible tax policy and practice and how it can be applied by corporate and investors. &#xB7; Hold private sector actors to account for paying their fair share. &#xB7;  Build and enhance the social contract between private sector tax payers, governments and the whole of society.</narrative>
  </description>
